parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic shoulder belt can lead to inadequate restraint of occupants in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seatbelt comes loose while driving
the seatbelt retractor fails
the seatbelt locks up
the automatic shoulder belt fails to restrain occupants
the seatbelt motors fail
the shoulder belt fails prior to recall
the automatic shoulder belt comes across the driver's or passenger's neck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially during panic stops.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle continues to roll forward despite applying the brakes
the brakes continuously squeal even after repair or replacement
the brakes fail to respond during panic stops.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn-out brake pads and resurfaced rotors can reduce the effectiveness of the brake system, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The brake pads wear out prematurely
the rotors need to be resurfaced frequently
the brakes squeal or make unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of suspension components, such as springs, can cause loss of control or accidents, especially at higher speeds.
symptoms: The spring snaps and flies out from beneath the car
no warning sounds or feel before the failure
the part is difficult to find due to high demand.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical systems, such as turn signals, can cause confusion or accidents, especially at intersections.
symptoms: The lights go to bright when turn signals are put on
the turn signals malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of door latches can cause doors to open unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The door latch fails
the door opens unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater blower switch can cause a fire hazard due to overheating and melting of the switch and surrounding wiring, potentially leading to a vehicle fire or electrical system failure.
symptoms: The heater blower switch melts and becomes inoperative
the wiring connected to the switch melts
the heater blower fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic shoulder belt to retract can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash, as the belt may not provide proper restraint.
symptoms: The driver's side automatic shoulder belt fails to retract
the belt remains loose or stuck in an extended position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause a loss of power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine cuts off at a stop
the engine requires spark plug removal and air drying to restart
the vehicle stalls or dies suddenly.
